						<p>Front wall of the Vishṇu temple.</p>						

						<p>This undated epigraph may be assigned to the 17th century on the basis of palaeography.</p>						

						<p>Built in. The extant portion specifies that 5 <hi rend="italic">(ēdumu)</hi> of land in extent belongs to god <hi rend="italic">(dēvara-chēnu).</hi></p>						

